<span class="displaytext"><b>hillary up 7 points since last month, now leads nearest dem by roughly 2-1 margin </b> <p>(candidate full) has significantly widened her lead in the (PARTY NAME) primary to 22 points, leading her nearest rival by a roughly 2-1 margin, according to a new cbs news/ny times poll released today. the poll, in the field through wednesday, confirms the significant increases for (candidate last) also shown in a series of other recent polls. </p><p>specifically, the new poll shows:<br/> </p><ul> <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">hillary's lead over her nearest (PARTY NAME) rival has jumped to 22 points (46-24), from 15 last month (39-24).</li> <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">hillary's share of the (PARTY NAME) primary vote increased 7 points to 46 from 39 last month.</li> <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">73 percent of all (PARTY NAME) polled believe hillary can win the general election (an increase of 9 percent since january), compared to 56 percent for her nearest rival.</li> <li style="margin-bottom: 1em;">hillary's favorable rating among all (PARTY NAME) polled is over 20 points higher than her nearest rival ((candidate last) 65 percent; (candidate last) 44; (candidate last) 40).</li> </ul> <p>"this continued widening of hillary's lead shows that americans are increasingly ready for change and that they are confident hillary is ready to lead," said (candidate last) chief strategist and pollster mark penn. </p><p>today's poll comes on the heels of a usa today poll showing hillary leading the primary by 15 points, a cnn poll showing her up by 14, and a newsweek poll showing her beating every (PARTY NAME) and (PARTY NAME) candidate in head-to-head matchups. </p><p>the latest gallup poll also shows (candidate last)'s favorability climbing -- now 53 percent overall, up 8 points since last month.</p></span>



